{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4938ae6-e013-43b7-a217-d9146bc83a34","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int value) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **MSTest & NUnit** both use `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n- **xUnit** uses a `Skip` property on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`\n- **TUnit** uses `[Skip(\"reason\")]`\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36180db7-1f60-4fe4-b4db-e1d56c7e54aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question about test framework APIs. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":330,"requestId":"0420:1CF5FA:1EA9065:229F121:69E81E65"},"id":"9f092e40-3e82-4585-bda9-6000e53b512f","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:03:40.368Z","parentId":"ee29da82-f11e-4ea6-9b31-9e6c37ec2a28"}
